1
00:00:12,762 --> 00:00:14,431
I've been thinking.

2
00:00:14,514 --> 00:00:15,348
Yes?

3
00:00:16,474 --> 00:00:19,394
You said the Wunderkinder run
the Church of Eternal Salvation.

4
00:00:19,936 --> 00:00:22,814
If they can do it, why can't we?

5
00:00:23,356 --> 00:00:25,316
We're miracle children,
I mean, adults too.

6
00:00:26,401 --> 00:00:28,862
Has your dream evolved
from con artist to cult leader?

7
00:00:29,446 --> 00:00:32,699
If the entire congregation
each gave a 10,000-won offering,

8
00:00:33,199 --> 00:00:34,325
how much would that be?

9
00:00:34,951 --> 00:00:35,952
Not to mention tithes.

10
00:00:36,036 --> 00:00:39,914
And those who offer up their entire
life savings to live communally.

11
00:00:39,998 --> 00:00:41,124
Roughly speaking…

12
00:00:43,835 --> 00:00:46,838
Sheesh, I can't even do the math.

13
00:00:46,921 --> 00:00:50,633
Hey, if we play our cards right,
we could make more money than Uri Geller.

14
00:00:50,717 --> 00:00:53,470
I don't want to use my powers
on something like that.

15
00:00:53,553 --> 00:00:55,597
You're too naive.

16
00:00:55,680 --> 00:00:58,058
- This is your problem.
- Seriously?

17
00:00:58,141 --> 00:01:00,852
Powers are meant to be used.

18
00:01:01,603 --> 00:01:04,230
What's taking Lady Trainwreck
and Mr. Oddball so long?

19
00:01:04,731 --> 00:01:06,941
I can't just clock out before dessert.

20
00:01:07,484 --> 00:01:08,318
Quiet.

21
00:01:09,110 --> 00:01:10,445
I am being quiet.

22
00:01:10,528 --> 00:01:11,446
My phone's ringing.

23
00:01:18,119 --> 00:01:19,079
Hello?

24
00:01:20,830 --> 00:01:21,706
Hey!

25
00:01:22,248 --> 00:01:23,666
I'll take this call outside.

26
00:01:28,963 --> 00:01:31,049
Yes, Mother. Have you had dinner?

27
00:01:32,092 --> 00:01:33,343
Me? You know, same old.

28
00:01:33,426 --> 00:01:35,970
Well, the guys at City Hall

29
00:01:36,054 --> 00:01:39,516
kept begging and begging,
asking me to please help out with work.

30
00:01:40,016 --> 00:01:41,476
No, I'm a freelancer.

31
00:01:41,976 --> 00:01:45,063
These days, all the really talented folks
work freelance.

32
00:02:01,704 --> 00:02:03,081
One second, Mom.

33
00:02:14,926 --> 00:02:16,469
Mom, I'll call you back.

34
00:02:17,971 --> 00:02:20,223
She teleports when her heart beats fast.

35
00:02:21,349 --> 00:02:23,184
As long as her heart doesn't beat fast,

36
00:02:24,018 --> 00:02:25,562
that woman can't do anything.

37
00:02:53,423 --> 00:02:55,550
OUR MASTER
MAY YOU ALSO MASTER HAPPINESS

38
00:03:48,228 --> 00:03:51,856
THE WONDERFOOLS

39
00:03:53,149 --> 00:03:57,320
EPISODE 6
ALL ROADS LEAD TO CHAE-NI

40
00:03:58,738 --> 00:04:00,949
However, our shepherd has told us,

41
00:04:01,032 --> 00:04:03,576
"Everything is possible
for the one who believes."

42
00:04:04,619 --> 00:04:06,037
Today, right here,

43
00:04:06,120 --> 00:04:08,164
we will witness the glory of a miracle.

44
00:04:08,873 --> 00:04:10,500
Through the marked one,

45
00:04:10,583 --> 00:04:12,502
our shepherd Kim Pal-ho.

46
00:04:13,127 --> 00:04:14,128
Today,

47
00:04:14,754 --> 00:04:16,673
before our very eyes,

48
00:04:16,756 --> 00:04:18,758
our brother will stand tall
on his two feet.

49
00:04:20,009 --> 00:04:21,886
- I believe.
- I believe.

50
00:04:30,103 --> 00:04:31,020
Jae-won.

51
00:04:42,949 --> 00:04:43,783
He stood up!

52
00:04:59,966 --> 00:05:01,134
Believe!

53
00:05:01,217 --> 00:05:06,097
A living faith will make us stand tall.

54
00:05:06,180 --> 00:05:10,810
And it shall deliver us
from the dominion of death.

55
00:05:14,147 --> 00:05:15,815
It's a miracle!

56
00:05:24,073 --> 00:05:26,326
Amen! It's a miracle!

57
00:05:26,409 --> 00:05:27,827
- Hallelujah!
- Amen!

58
00:05:27,910 --> 00:05:33,166
Heaven and earth will pass away,
but my words will never pass away.

59
00:05:33,791 --> 00:05:36,502
- The prophecy of the end draws near.
- It's a miracle!

60
00:05:36,586 --> 00:05:40,214
And only a few
tickets to salvation remain.

61
00:05:40,298 --> 00:05:44,177
Show us your sincerity.
Show us your conviction.

62
00:05:44,260 --> 00:05:45,845
Hallelujah!

63
00:05:50,183 --> 00:05:51,601
Hallelujah!

64
00:05:51,684 --> 00:05:53,144
Hallelujah!

65
00:05:54,354 --> 00:05:56,147
Hallelujah!

66
00:05:57,440 --> 00:05:59,859
Amen!

67
00:05:59,942 --> 00:06:02,320
Shepherd!

68
00:06:13,498 --> 00:06:14,874
Their end goal is money.

69
00:06:16,501 --> 00:06:19,379
They're using the Wunderkinder's powers
to perform miracles.

70
00:06:21,089 --> 00:06:22,548
Witnessing these miracles,

71
00:06:22,632 --> 00:06:25,843
the congregation blindly believes
they're revelations from God.

72
00:06:26,552 --> 00:06:29,430
Dozens of new members
are joining the church every day.

73
00:06:30,890 --> 00:06:32,433
Ha Won-do, that fellow.

74
00:06:33,142 --> 00:06:36,896
He found those poor children again
and is using them to panhandle.

75
00:06:37,397 --> 00:06:41,275
And it's clear enough
what he'll try to do with that money.

76
00:06:41,776 --> 00:06:45,780
But he'll need more than just money
to start the experiments again.

77
00:06:46,697 --> 00:06:50,118
Don't you think there must be
someone more powerful behind all this?

78
00:07:13,933 --> 00:07:14,767
What's going on?

79
00:07:14,851 --> 00:07:17,812
He is currently carrying out
a crucial but dangerous revelation.

80
00:07:17,895 --> 00:07:21,649
He'd like the shepherd and you two sisters
to stay inside until he gives the word.

81
00:08:16,746 --> 00:08:18,915
Inject more of the drug
before she wakes up.

82
00:08:19,624 --> 00:08:21,292
We don't know how much she's had.

83
00:08:22,335 --> 00:08:23,169
It may be fatal--

84
00:08:38,476 --> 00:08:41,062
So there really was a successful subject.

85
00:08:41,145 --> 00:08:43,981
Inject the maximum dose.
It doesn't matter if she dies.

86
00:08:44,065 --> 00:08:45,983
And tie the specimen up just in case.

87
00:08:54,784 --> 00:08:57,328
What?

88
00:08:57,995 --> 00:08:59,956
What is this?

89
00:09:01,415 --> 00:09:03,834
What the… What is this?

90
00:09:04,961 --> 00:09:07,380
What… Damn it, where…

91
00:09:10,091 --> 00:09:11,634
This looks like…

92
00:09:13,678 --> 00:09:18,307
one of those secret labs you see
in cartoons, run by a mad scientist.

93
00:09:19,934 --> 00:09:21,227
This must be that place.

94
00:09:22,228 --> 00:09:24,146
The main branch of Boon the King Duck!

95
00:09:24,230 --> 00:09:25,314
Prepare more drugs.

96
00:09:25,398 --> 00:09:26,232
Yes.

97
00:09:29,860 --> 00:09:30,820
You.

98
00:09:31,320 --> 00:09:32,154
I saw you.

99
00:09:32,238 --> 00:09:33,197
That's right.

100
00:09:33,281 --> 00:09:35,825
I can tell you're the boss around here.

101
00:09:36,450 --> 00:09:37,702
Oh, come on!

102
00:09:37,785 --> 00:09:41,414
Why would you kidnap me like this?
Are you nuts?

103
00:09:41,998 --> 00:09:43,332
I had something to retrieve.

104
00:09:44,667 --> 00:09:45,501
Retrieve?

105
00:09:45,585 --> 00:09:48,004
Your heart belongs to someone else.

106
00:09:55,803 --> 00:09:57,179
Hey, lady.

107
00:09:57,680 --> 00:10:00,099
What's with the service here, huh?

108
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:02,852
Aren't you going to offer me coffee
or something?

109
00:10:03,769 --> 00:10:07,732
Or black tea, or green tea, or something?

110
00:10:07,815 --> 00:10:10,985
Don't you have anything with caffeine?

111
00:10:11,819 --> 00:10:13,029
COFFEE JELLY

112
00:10:22,496 --> 00:10:24,081
Hold it! Wait.

113
00:10:24,832 --> 00:10:26,459
Give me some time to think.

114
00:10:30,504 --> 00:10:32,632
Is this jelly caffeine-free?

115
00:10:33,507 --> 00:10:35,176
Hey, wait.

116
00:10:37,094 --> 00:10:39,722
Here it comes!

117
00:10:39,805 --> 00:10:41,223
Here it comes!

118
00:10:42,892 --> 00:10:45,478
She's over there! Get her!

119
00:10:46,062 --> 00:10:47,938
- Why's it so…
- Hurry! Grab her!

120
00:10:49,106 --> 00:10:50,232
- She's there!
- Get her!

121
00:10:50,316 --> 00:10:51,609
- That way!
- There she is!

122
00:10:52,193 --> 00:10:54,236
Catch her!

123
00:10:54,320 --> 00:10:55,404
Don't come any closer.

124
00:10:55,488 --> 00:10:56,447
Get her!

125
00:11:00,576 --> 00:11:01,869
Back off!

126
00:11:05,831 --> 00:11:08,000
Man, this is driving me crazy.

127
00:11:08,084 --> 00:11:10,086
Hold it right there.

128
00:11:10,169 --> 00:11:11,671
Time out!

129
00:11:16,801 --> 00:11:18,803
- What the heck?
- She just disappeared.

130
00:11:19,679 --> 00:11:20,846
Where did she go?

131
00:11:26,936 --> 00:11:29,271
PERSONAL RECORD CARD
3972

132
00:11:37,863 --> 00:11:40,533
It looks like the side effects
are getting to you too.

133
00:11:41,534 --> 00:11:43,619
You know it's only
a matter of time, don't you?

134
00:11:46,205 --> 00:11:48,165
Just bring me the Child of Eternity.

135
00:11:48,666 --> 00:11:50,334
Then you can live too.

136
00:11:53,087 --> 00:11:54,046
It turns out…

137
00:11:56,132 --> 00:11:57,717
that you have family.

138
00:12:07,852 --> 00:12:09,812
SERIAL NUMBER: 3972
NAME: KO EUN-SAN

139
00:12:24,285 --> 00:12:26,203
FATHER: KO MIN-SEOK
DECEASED

140
00:12:26,287 --> 00:12:29,707
MOTHER: JANG YUN-HUI
DOMESTIC RESIDENCE

141
00:12:59,945 --> 00:13:02,573
I finally found you, Master.

142
00:13:06,869 --> 00:13:08,037
Why did you do it?

143
00:13:08,788 --> 00:13:10,623
Why did you do that to me?

144
00:13:14,084 --> 00:13:15,336
I won't say

145
00:13:16,670 --> 00:13:17,630
I'm sorry.

146
00:13:26,096 --> 00:13:27,598
Is this why you were nice to me?

147
00:13:29,266 --> 00:13:30,226
Yes.

148
00:13:30,309 --> 00:13:31,894
That heart.

149
00:13:32,812 --> 00:13:36,732
If not for that, you would never
have helped us to begin with?

150
00:13:39,193 --> 00:13:40,027
I wouldn't have.

151
00:13:44,448 --> 00:13:45,366
Come with me.

152
00:13:45,991 --> 00:13:47,743
Come with me and fix this.

153
00:13:48,410 --> 00:13:50,412
If I go over there again,

154
00:13:50,913 --> 00:13:53,457
I have nowhere else to run to.

155
00:13:54,542 --> 00:13:57,127
Master, go and fix it for me.

156
00:13:58,838 --> 00:14:00,923
I thought you were on my side,

157
00:14:01,006 --> 00:14:02,508
no matter what!

158
00:14:07,513 --> 00:14:08,430
What's this, then?

159
00:14:10,474 --> 00:14:11,976
COFFEE JELLY

160
00:14:21,986 --> 00:14:26,323
Instead of giving me this, you shouldn't
have handed me over in the first place!

161
00:15:17,249 --> 00:15:18,459
No!

162
00:15:20,920 --> 00:15:21,754
Come on!

163
00:15:22,254 --> 00:15:24,715
You should have brought him with you!

164
00:15:26,091 --> 00:15:28,052
Why's my damn nose running now?

165
00:15:29,428 --> 00:15:30,679
It can't be helped.

166
00:15:30,763 --> 00:15:32,139
Since it's come to this…

167
00:15:34,266 --> 00:15:37,269
I'm going to have to find
my own way to survive--

168
00:15:39,229 --> 00:15:42,274
Lee Un-jeong, you son of a…

169
00:16:24,066 --> 00:16:27,403
Don't let her get too drowsy or too alert.

170
00:16:27,486 --> 00:16:31,156
Just keep her heart beating
slowly but steadily.

171
00:16:31,240 --> 00:16:32,449
Understood.

172
00:16:40,124 --> 00:16:42,543
After all that criticism about what I did

173
00:16:42,626 --> 00:16:45,295
with sick children
and how I should pay for my sins,

174
00:16:46,088 --> 00:16:48,090
it seems your grandmother
wasn't any better.

175
00:16:49,425 --> 00:16:50,843
You're wrong.

176
00:16:52,511 --> 00:16:54,179
My grandma

177
00:16:55,097 --> 00:16:57,725
knows what she did wrong.

178
00:16:58,684 --> 00:17:00,352
But you people

179
00:17:01,228 --> 00:17:02,688
damn well don't.

180
00:17:03,689 --> 00:17:07,443
Don't lump her in with you
because it's insulting.

181
00:17:07,526 --> 00:17:09,611
Simply by sacrificing your life,

182
00:17:09,695 --> 00:17:12,448
we could save so many others.

183
00:17:15,034 --> 00:17:17,327
Do you think
your grandma would accept that?

184
00:17:18,162 --> 00:17:19,621
No, she wouldn't.

185
00:17:19,705 --> 00:17:21,915
She'd just want to save you.

186
00:17:22,583 --> 00:17:24,835
Even if it meant
all those people would die,

187
00:17:24,918 --> 00:17:26,462
she'd want to save you.

188
00:17:29,173 --> 00:17:30,883
But the question is…

189
00:17:33,177 --> 00:17:36,555
are you someone who's worth taking away

190
00:17:37,056 --> 00:17:38,515
other people's chances?

191
00:17:41,268 --> 00:17:43,729
Are you someone
who has a definitive reason to live,

192
00:17:43,812 --> 00:17:46,940
even if it means forgoing countless lives?

193
00:17:48,567 --> 00:17:50,194
Are you really that worthy?

194
00:17:56,617 --> 00:17:57,534
No.

195
00:17:58,035 --> 00:17:59,995
You're nothing.

196
00:18:00,496 --> 00:18:02,623
You aren't worthy.

197
00:18:04,083 --> 00:18:04,917
You

198
00:18:06,376 --> 00:18:09,463
do not deserve that heart.

199
00:18:28,107 --> 00:18:28,941
Cheong!

200
00:18:29,691 --> 00:18:31,193
Honey! Cheong!

201
00:18:31,693 --> 00:18:32,778
We saved this for you.

202
00:18:32,861 --> 00:18:33,862
Great. Thanks, Cheong.

203
00:18:34,905 --> 00:18:37,616
It's dangerous. We have to go now.
Let's hurry and pack.

204
00:18:38,659 --> 00:18:40,994
What nonsense are you up to now?

205
00:18:41,495 --> 00:18:43,122
Where would we go?

206
00:18:43,622 --> 00:18:46,708
Don't you know Dad by now?
He wants to go on a trip.

207
00:18:49,336 --> 00:18:51,547
That's not it. We're in grave danger.

208
00:18:51,630 --> 00:18:55,134
We need to go somewhere else.
How about your parents' home?

209
00:18:55,217 --> 00:18:57,761
What's so dangerous
about this place and how?

210
00:18:57,845 --> 00:19:00,639
Just ask him where he wants to go.
That'd be quicker.

211
00:19:02,558 --> 00:19:03,809
Cheong, listen carefully.

212
00:19:04,768 --> 00:19:05,894
The truth is that I,

213
00:19:06,603 --> 00:19:08,647
for reasons I can't disclose,

214
00:19:08,730 --> 00:19:11,108
gained an ability that I can't disclose.

215
00:19:11,608 --> 00:19:13,110
Some people I can't name

216
00:19:13,193 --> 00:19:16,280
might do something terrible to me
that I can't disclose, so--

217
00:19:16,363 --> 00:19:17,281
Did you get a loan?

218
00:19:17,364 --> 00:19:20,826
No, I didn't! Oh, for crying out loud!

219
00:19:21,577 --> 00:19:22,452
That's not it!

220
00:19:24,454 --> 00:19:28,167
Fine. I admit that I've never been
very reliable. I apologize for that.

221
00:19:28,250 --> 00:19:30,502
But can't you just, for once…

222
00:19:30,586 --> 00:19:32,963
Can't you just trust me for once?

223
00:19:33,046 --> 00:19:35,174
How dare you throw the phrase

224
00:19:35,674 --> 00:19:37,718
"for once" in my face again?

225
00:19:38,802 --> 00:19:41,513
Once was when you took early severance,
or bought stocks,

226
00:19:41,597 --> 00:19:43,640
invested in cicada larva mucin,
snail extract…

227
00:19:43,724 --> 00:19:47,060
And Lion's Mane Mushroom granular powder
and germanium bracelets.

228
00:19:47,144 --> 00:19:49,313
I'm telling you, it's not like that!

229
00:19:49,396 --> 00:19:51,899
This is not a drill!

230
00:19:52,858 --> 00:19:57,613
I just saw Lady Trainwreck Eun Chae-ni
being kidnapped with my own two eyes.

231
00:19:57,696 --> 00:20:00,282
Then you should report it to the police.

232
00:20:01,366 --> 00:20:03,076
Go do your homework.

233
00:20:04,244 --> 00:20:05,287
I told you.

234
00:20:05,370 --> 00:20:08,373
I can't do that for reasons
I can't possibly tell you.

235
00:20:08,457 --> 00:20:09,666
Then how about

236
00:20:09,750 --> 00:20:12,252
we get a divorce for reasons
we can't disclose?

237
00:20:14,213 --> 00:20:16,215
Don't be like that, okay?

238
00:20:16,715 --> 00:20:19,218
Why don't we stay
at your father's house for a while--

239
00:20:19,301 --> 00:20:21,261
If you can pay for their new boiler, sure.

240
00:20:23,180 --> 00:20:25,557
There's a large order from the Church.

241
00:20:26,516 --> 00:20:27,351
Say what?

242
00:20:28,393 --> 00:20:31,396
I guess they want to hold
a grand service before the apocalypse.

243
00:20:31,480 --> 00:20:34,024
How romantic.

244
00:20:34,524 --> 00:20:36,443
To perish surrounded by flowers.

245
00:20:36,526 --> 00:20:39,154
No, they're a cult.
We can't get involved. They're harmful.

246
00:20:39,238 --> 00:20:40,072
Dangerous!

247
00:20:41,657 --> 00:20:44,493
The most harmful thing in my life is you.

248
00:20:46,245 --> 00:20:48,288
Aren't you scared of
what might happen to me?

249
00:20:48,372 --> 00:20:49,831
Know what I'm scared of?

250
00:20:49,915 --> 00:20:52,626
Not being able to pay
for Cheong's cram school.

251
00:20:53,126 --> 00:20:56,296
And I'm terrified of our landlord
raising the shop's security deposit.

252
00:21:04,263 --> 00:21:05,138
Is that so?

253
00:21:06,139 --> 00:21:07,015
Am I

254
00:21:08,850 --> 00:21:10,435
that harmful to you?

255
00:21:12,521 --> 00:21:13,981
So that's how it is?

256
00:21:15,607 --> 00:21:16,566
Fine. I get it.

257
00:21:17,442 --> 00:21:18,986
Divorce, did you say?

258
00:21:20,237 --> 00:21:21,321
Let's do it.

259
00:21:23,907 --> 00:21:28,120
Do you think I just put up with everything
because I don't have a temper?

260
00:21:28,203 --> 00:21:31,456
Do I seem weak because I put up
with everything as the man of the house?

261
00:21:31,540 --> 00:21:32,541
Hey, Moon Mi-hui.

262
00:21:32,624 --> 00:21:36,461
I still have some fight left in me.
I'm not finished yet!

263
00:21:37,838 --> 00:21:38,839
Forget it.

264
00:21:39,798 --> 00:21:41,800
While we're at it, let's just end things.

265
00:21:42,467 --> 00:21:45,637
I'm sick and tired of living
so pathetically like this too.

266
00:21:45,721 --> 00:21:47,097
Sick and tired.

267
00:22:02,654 --> 00:22:05,699
Keep it down!

268
00:22:25,635 --> 00:22:29,306
- Everything will be fine if I just die?
- It keeps sticking.

269
00:22:31,641 --> 00:22:33,852
If I die,

270
00:22:35,645 --> 00:22:38,440
the world will change?

271
00:22:40,233 --> 00:22:42,986
Think of it as paying
for your grandmother's sins.

272
00:22:44,988 --> 00:22:46,156
Who are you?

273
00:22:46,239 --> 00:22:47,866
In any case,

274
00:22:48,367 --> 00:22:51,661
you lived the past 20 years
thanks to your rich grandmother.

275
00:22:51,745 --> 00:22:53,538
Are these

276
00:22:55,082 --> 00:22:57,000
my own thoughts?

277
00:22:58,043 --> 00:23:00,128
So if you can hear me, answer me.

278
00:23:01,546 --> 00:23:02,547
Tell me that you'll…

279
00:23:05,092 --> 00:23:06,176
die for us.

280
00:23:11,348 --> 00:23:13,266
For you…

281
00:23:14,518 --> 00:23:15,769
Die…

282
00:23:19,564 --> 00:23:20,399
gladly.

283
00:23:22,776 --> 00:23:24,319
Gladly…

284
00:23:37,624 --> 00:23:38,667
Die!

285
00:24:36,558 --> 00:24:38,435
I can't see anything.

286
00:24:38,518 --> 00:24:39,352
Seriously?

287
00:24:39,436 --> 00:24:42,397
- Just tell me how.
- Why are you wearing those?

288
00:24:42,481 --> 00:24:45,066
You can't see
because you're wearing these!

289
00:24:45,150 --> 00:24:46,776
That hurts!

290
00:24:46,860 --> 00:24:49,613
Hey, I'm not stupid.
I'm telling you, I can take these off.

291
00:24:49,696 --> 00:24:52,949
- For crying out loud.
- Just tell me to take them off.

292
00:24:58,997 --> 00:25:00,123
Is Eunie well?

293
00:25:00,749 --> 00:25:03,043
Tell her it's time to move back home,
if she can.

294
00:25:03,126 --> 00:25:05,170
She can stop being mad at me later.

295
00:25:05,253 --> 00:25:06,338
Sure.

296
00:25:06,838 --> 00:25:07,672
Sorry?

297
00:25:09,382 --> 00:25:10,550
Yes, ma'am.

298
00:25:12,761 --> 00:25:16,264
She's lost her mind.
Did she sleep at Master's house or what?

299
00:25:16,348 --> 00:25:18,725
I packed some food,
so take it and go home.

300
00:25:18,808 --> 00:25:20,227
She must be bored alone.

301
00:25:20,310 --> 00:25:21,144
I'll be back.

302
00:25:22,771 --> 00:25:24,064
See you later.

303
00:25:25,732 --> 00:25:26,816
Goodbye, ma'am.

304
00:25:28,318 --> 00:25:30,779
- What's going on?
- Did something happen?

305
00:25:30,862 --> 00:25:32,531
Auntie, I'm going out for a bit.

306
00:25:32,614 --> 00:25:33,823
Okay.

307
00:25:37,827 --> 00:25:39,412
You're completely fine.

308
00:25:40,080 --> 00:25:41,456
You didn't get kidnapped.

309
00:25:57,764 --> 00:26:00,976
I'll escort you home
after a hot cup of tea, Madam.

310
00:26:01,685 --> 00:26:05,730
I just need you to tell me where he is.
I really need to see him.

311
00:26:05,814 --> 00:26:08,024
He's overseas,
so you can't see him anyway.

312
00:26:08,108 --> 00:26:11,444
Overseas where? When is he coming back?
I can go to him instead.

313
00:26:11,528 --> 00:26:13,488
I'm not at liberty to disclose that.

314
00:26:15,991 --> 00:26:20,495
An overseas trip with a vague schedule
usually means a trip to the hospital.

315
00:26:22,539 --> 00:26:23,373
Where is he?

316
00:26:31,923 --> 00:26:33,633
It'd be best for you to leave now.

317
00:26:33,717 --> 00:26:35,093
Should I find out for myself?

318
00:26:42,058 --> 00:26:42,892
Yes, it's me.

319
00:26:43,393 --> 00:26:45,770
I found out
who got Ha Won-do out on parole.

320
00:26:49,899 --> 00:26:51,484
It was Chairman Nam Sun-gyu.

321
00:26:53,278 --> 00:26:55,447
He's at the Church
of Eternal Salvation now.

322
00:27:08,084 --> 00:27:10,670
Neither Master nor Chae-ni is answering.

323
00:27:12,672 --> 00:27:13,548
Mr. Son.

324
00:27:14,132 --> 00:27:17,218
Do you think they fell in love
and ran away together?

325
00:27:17,302 --> 00:27:19,054
This is your problem.

326
00:27:19,554 --> 00:27:22,182
That's seriously the genre you see
for those two?

327
00:27:22,682 --> 00:27:27,020
Don't you think a thriller or action film
with a deadly chase is far more likely?

328
00:27:28,563 --> 00:27:30,065
Or a kidnapping.

329
00:27:30,148 --> 00:27:32,233
But neither of them is answering.

330
00:27:32,317 --> 00:27:33,902
They could've spent the night--

331
00:27:33,985 --> 00:27:36,196
The truth is,
I saw Chae-ni being kidnapped.

332
00:27:39,240 --> 00:27:42,494
Turns out Oddball is in league
with the Church of Eternal Salvation.

333
00:27:43,411 --> 00:27:45,789
That jerk totally played us.

334
00:27:46,289 --> 00:27:48,750
There you go with your lying again.

335
00:27:56,174 --> 00:27:58,259
I am Kang Ro-bin.

336
00:28:03,014 --> 00:28:04,849
Oddball kidnapped Chae-ni.

337
00:28:05,475 --> 00:28:07,102
The Wunderkinder and the Church.

338
00:28:07,185 --> 00:28:09,979
He's in league with them
and kidnapped Chae-ni!

339
00:28:13,149 --> 00:28:15,235
What?! What do we do?

340
00:28:15,318 --> 00:28:16,736
What can we do?

341
00:28:17,737 --> 00:28:20,990
We hide.
Stay out of Oddball's sight for a while.

342
00:28:21,074 --> 00:28:23,785
But what about Chae-ni?
You said she was taken.

343
00:28:23,868 --> 00:28:26,413
What if they dissect her or something?

344
00:28:26,496 --> 00:28:27,497
What can we do?

345
00:28:28,123 --> 00:28:29,290
That's her damn fate.

346
00:28:30,875 --> 00:28:33,920
You can't say that, Mr. Son.

347
00:28:34,003 --> 00:28:36,798
We already abandoned Chae-ni once.
You want to do it again?

348
00:28:37,590 --> 00:28:39,968
Then what?
Are you going to fight them alone?

349
00:28:41,261 --> 00:28:42,137
Wait a minute.

350
00:28:43,805 --> 00:28:45,932
I'm going to see Master.
I'll ask him myself.

351
00:28:46,015 --> 00:28:48,017
Just sit down!

352
00:28:49,811 --> 00:28:52,147
You're not coming, are you?
Then I'll go alone.

353
00:28:52,230 --> 00:28:53,940
For heaven's sake.

354
00:28:54,023 --> 00:28:56,234
What could you do?
Are you trying to get killed?

355
00:28:56,317 --> 00:28:57,777
You're the biggest coward ever.

356
00:28:58,528 --> 00:29:01,281
What could you do
when you'd faint before ever saving her?

357
00:29:01,364 --> 00:29:02,949
How could you ever save anyone?

358
00:29:06,244 --> 00:29:07,996
Let go. That's way too hard.

359
00:29:08,621 --> 00:29:09,622
You're right.

360
00:29:10,123 --> 00:29:11,374
I'm a coward

361
00:29:11,958 --> 00:29:12,959
who's slow

362
00:29:13,668 --> 00:29:14,919
and tactless.

363
00:29:15,420 --> 00:29:18,798
Everyone in the world thinks
that I'm nothing but a nuisance.

364
00:29:21,217 --> 00:29:22,677
Everyone except Chae-ni.

365
00:29:23,928 --> 00:29:25,054
Twenty-three!

366
00:29:25,555 --> 00:29:26,931
Twenty-four!

367
00:29:27,432 --> 00:29:28,767
Twenty-five!

368
00:29:29,267 --> 00:29:30,602
Twenty-six!

369
00:29:30,685 --> 00:29:32,270
Twenty-seven!

370
00:29:32,771 --> 00:29:34,147
Twenty-eight!

371
00:29:34,647 --> 00:29:36,107
Twenty-nine!

372
00:29:36,691 --> 00:29:37,692
Thirty!

373
00:29:37,776 --> 00:29:38,860
Oh, come on!

374
00:29:39,444 --> 00:29:41,488
- What the heck?
- What's wrong with him?

375
00:29:42,739 --> 00:29:44,199
What are you doing?

376
00:29:44,282 --> 00:29:45,825
Is this that hard?

377
00:29:46,326 --> 00:29:47,619
Get a hold of yourselves!

378
00:29:47,702 --> 00:29:50,955
- Semester just started. Snap out of it!
- Hey, stop messing up.

379
00:29:52,707 --> 00:29:54,292
Next, 50 times! How many times?

380
00:29:54,375 --> 00:29:55,960
Fifty!

381
00:29:56,044 --> 00:29:57,420
Forty-three!

382
00:29:57,921 --> 00:29:59,088
Forty-four!

383
00:29:59,714 --> 00:30:00,965
Forty-five!

384
00:30:01,466 --> 00:30:02,884
Forty-six!

385
00:30:02,967 --> 00:30:04,260
Forty-seven!

386
00:30:05,386 --> 00:30:06,554
Forty-eight!

387
00:30:06,638 --> 00:30:07,722
Forty-nine!

388
00:30:08,556 --> 00:30:09,641
Fifty!

389
00:30:11,017 --> 00:30:11,976
Hey!

390
00:30:21,110 --> 00:30:22,570
Hey, Sap!

391
00:30:23,196 --> 00:30:24,864
How can you eat right now?

392
00:30:25,907 --> 00:30:27,742
Enjoy your meals, guys. I'm sorry.

393
00:30:29,786 --> 00:30:30,954
You idiot.

394
00:30:31,621 --> 00:30:33,498
- This looks good.
- Yeah, enjoy.

395
00:30:35,124 --> 00:30:36,417
Enjoy your meals.

396
00:30:38,628 --> 00:30:40,255
- Eat up.
- Hey, this is good.

397
00:30:56,855 --> 00:30:58,106
This fried egg is good.

398
00:31:00,024 --> 00:31:01,568
From now on,

399
00:31:02,151 --> 00:31:03,486
you eat lunch with me.

400
00:31:03,570 --> 00:31:05,530
What? Okay.

401
00:31:07,490 --> 00:31:10,618
Hey, Sappy Sap of Class 3. You idiot--

402
00:31:10,702 --> 00:31:11,828
Hey, don't.

403
00:31:11,911 --> 00:31:14,289
- Cut it out.
- I have something to tell you.

404
00:31:14,372 --> 00:31:16,124
Come on. Let's talk.

405
00:31:16,207 --> 00:31:18,251
- Let's go. It'll be quick.
- What is it?

406
00:31:23,298 --> 00:31:24,215
Let's eat.

407
00:31:40,982 --> 00:31:42,817
That was the first time

408
00:31:42,901 --> 00:31:44,277
someone stood by me.

409
00:31:44,861 --> 00:31:46,946
Chae-ni was the first person
to do that for me.

410
00:31:48,615 --> 00:31:50,283
I see, Ro-bin.

411
00:31:51,075 --> 00:31:53,536
But how about you let me go
for such long stories?

412
00:31:54,037 --> 00:31:57,415
It hurts so much. It hurts, okay?

413
00:32:00,793 --> 00:32:02,545
If you're going to hide, go ahead.

414
00:32:04,422 --> 00:32:05,924
Hey, at least eat before you go.

415
00:32:06,007 --> 00:32:08,843
Hey, Chae-ni's grandma
packed this for us. Ro-bin!

416
00:32:09,344 --> 00:32:10,303
Hey!

417
00:32:10,386 --> 00:32:12,347
What? A letter of resignation?

418
00:32:12,430 --> 00:32:15,016
Yeah, he says he's going back to Seoul.

419
00:32:15,516 --> 00:32:19,437
Just like this, out of nowhere,
without a goodbye or a farewell party?

420
00:32:19,520 --> 00:32:23,816
This is why I told you not to warm up
to those cold-hearted city boys, Na-yeong.

421
00:32:25,443 --> 00:32:26,694
Heartless bastard.

422
00:32:31,199 --> 00:32:32,492
You scared me.

423
00:32:36,496 --> 00:32:39,123
See? He never intended to stick around.

424
00:32:45,755 --> 00:32:47,465
That bastard.

425
00:32:51,844 --> 00:32:53,721
Whoa, why? What? Why?

426
00:32:53,805 --> 00:32:54,931
Sir?

427
00:32:55,974 --> 00:32:58,184
Is he really going back to Seoul?

428
00:32:58,893 --> 00:32:59,727
Yes.

429
00:33:00,228 --> 00:33:01,437
He is. Why do you ask?

430
00:33:07,193 --> 00:33:08,069
Did he see?

431
00:33:11,364 --> 00:33:13,282
PLEASE DISPOSE OF THIS

432
00:33:42,729 --> 00:33:43,730
Where's Chae-ni?

433
00:33:45,148 --> 00:33:46,983
Go home. I don't know anything.

434
00:33:56,117 --> 00:33:58,077
There you go, stomping away again!

435
00:33:58,661 --> 00:34:01,873
City Hall guy!
I swear I'll report you to the police!

436
00:34:02,623 --> 00:34:03,875
The truth is,

437
00:34:04,917 --> 00:34:07,211
I've felt strong since earlier.

438
00:34:07,879 --> 00:34:09,422
But I'm just so upset

439
00:34:11,174 --> 00:34:13,801
that I can't seem to lose my strength.

440
00:34:21,267 --> 00:34:23,436
Put me down and let's talk.

441
00:34:23,519 --> 00:34:25,229
Tell me where Chae-ni is first.

442
00:34:25,855 --> 00:34:27,023
What did you do to her?

443
00:34:27,648 --> 00:34:31,027
Master, did you really
hand her over to them?

444
00:34:31,110 --> 00:34:32,361
Did you

445
00:34:33,154 --> 00:34:35,448
really betray us?

446
00:35:39,637 --> 00:35:40,555
Hello?

447
00:35:40,638 --> 00:35:43,891
Hey, Kang Ro-bin, where are you?
Did you go to see Oddball after all?

448
00:35:43,975 --> 00:35:48,771
The owner of Hearty House is going crazy
trying to find you and Chae-ni!

449
00:35:52,692 --> 00:35:54,485
I'm Eun Chae-ni's grandmother.

450
00:36:09,083 --> 00:36:09,959
Go ahead.

451
00:36:10,459 --> 00:36:12,503
I'd like to see you for a moment.

452
00:36:13,713 --> 00:36:15,173
Can you come over?

453
00:36:15,673 --> 00:36:16,841
You're okay, right?

454
00:36:16,924 --> 00:36:19,093
Please tell me you're okay!

455
00:36:19,177 --> 00:36:20,261
Hey! Hello?

456
00:36:20,344 --> 00:36:21,345
Mr. Son.

457
00:36:21,429 --> 00:36:22,763
Please insult me.

458
00:36:22,847 --> 00:36:24,515
Are you listening to me or not?

459
00:36:25,016 --> 00:36:27,476
I swear, you're dead meat when I find you!

460
00:37:11,979 --> 00:37:13,648
EUN CHAE-NI'S BUCKET LIST

461
00:37:16,275 --> 00:37:18,486
1. CLIMB KILIMANJARO
2. SEE THE NORTHERN LIGHTS

462
00:37:18,569 --> 00:37:20,738
3. SEE THE HELLUSION
WHEN THEY COME TO KOREA

463
00:37:20,821 --> 00:37:22,490
AND EXPLORE SEOUL WHILE I'M THERE

464
00:37:22,573 --> 00:37:23,658
4. KISS

465
00:37:26,869 --> 00:37:28,913
5. EAT A WHOLE CAKE
6. RIDE THE EAGLE FORTRESS

466
00:37:32,625 --> 00:37:35,378
9. DATE
10. LIVE PAST 30

467
00:37:38,047 --> 00:37:40,675
LIVE PAST 30

468
00:37:42,176 --> 00:37:45,930
Can I ask you something?

469
00:37:49,267 --> 00:37:51,978
Is Master one of the people

470
00:37:53,187 --> 00:37:54,939
I'd be saving?

471
00:37:55,731 --> 00:37:57,525
Are you referring to 3972?

472
00:37:58,484 --> 00:37:59,610
If so,

473
00:38:00,319 --> 00:38:02,363
you've already saved him.

474
00:38:03,072 --> 00:38:04,657
In return for handing you over,

475
00:38:05,157 --> 00:38:06,742
he got to meet his mom.

476
00:38:15,376 --> 00:38:16,419
What?

477
00:38:18,087 --> 00:38:19,547
If that's the case…

478
00:38:21,549 --> 00:38:23,467
I can't even be mad at him.

479
00:38:28,431 --> 00:38:29,890
His mom?

480
00:38:29,974 --> 00:38:32,268
I can't beat that.

481
00:38:45,156 --> 00:38:47,742
All done. Come out here.

482
00:38:54,040 --> 00:38:56,208
I heard from Eunie

483
00:38:57,293 --> 00:38:58,544
that you're a Wunderkinder.

484
00:39:01,839 --> 00:39:02,673
I'm sorry.

485
00:39:04,842 --> 00:39:06,302
I asked you here

486
00:39:06,385 --> 00:39:09,430
because this may be
my last chance to apologize.

487
00:39:12,641 --> 00:39:13,934
I wanted to make sure

488
00:39:15,436 --> 00:39:17,855
you had a home-cooked meal before leaving.

489
00:39:22,818 --> 00:39:25,738
I know this won't make up for anything,

490
00:39:27,073 --> 00:39:29,367
but I thought it was the least I could do.

491
00:39:30,701 --> 00:39:32,161
As you said,

492
00:39:33,662 --> 00:39:36,165
I don't think a meal
can make up for all those years.

493
00:39:38,167 --> 00:39:39,335
I'll be on my way now.

494
00:39:39,418 --> 00:39:40,920
Where is my Chae-ni?

495
00:39:43,839 --> 00:39:45,257
That's all I ask.

496
00:39:46,133 --> 00:39:47,301
Did you, by any chance,

497
00:39:48,135 --> 00:39:50,346
hand her over to Ha Won-do?

498
00:39:52,723 --> 00:39:56,143
I'm not asking you to save her.
I'll do the saving.

499
00:39:56,894 --> 00:39:59,188
Just tell me where Chae-ni is.

500
00:40:00,064 --> 00:40:01,065
Where is she now?

501
00:40:03,859 --> 00:40:04,735
It might

502
00:40:06,153 --> 00:40:07,154
already be too late.

503
00:40:07,238 --> 00:40:08,155
No.

504
00:40:08,656 --> 00:40:10,116
I know she's hanging in there.

505
00:40:11,242 --> 00:40:15,079
My baby doesn't go down that easily.
I know because she's my baby.

506
00:40:22,545 --> 00:40:23,379
My apologies.

507
00:40:36,600 --> 00:40:38,561
So he actually came when she asked.

508
00:40:39,145 --> 00:40:40,229
That traitor.

509
00:40:41,480 --> 00:40:43,983
And I guess you came
when asked, too, Mr. Son.

510
00:40:44,483 --> 00:40:45,734
You said you'd be hiding.

511
00:40:47,027 --> 00:40:47,862
Hey.

512
00:40:52,616 --> 00:40:53,534
What's going on?

513
00:40:54,285 --> 00:40:56,537
Did he already have it out with her?

514
00:40:57,037 --> 00:40:58,456
He's not in bad shape at all.

515
00:40:58,539 --> 00:40:59,373
Master!

516
00:41:01,250 --> 00:41:02,751
Kang Ro-bin, stay out of it!

517
00:41:05,337 --> 00:41:07,840
Where are you going?
Are you going to save Chae-ni?

518
00:41:07,923 --> 00:41:09,800
I bet 10,000 won that he isn't.

519
00:41:09,884 --> 00:41:13,596
- Are you really not going to save her?
- I bet my honor that he definitely won't.

520
00:41:20,478 --> 00:41:23,105
I thought it was all meaningless.

521
00:41:31,739 --> 00:41:33,657
Is that the child?

522
00:41:34,241 --> 00:41:35,075
Yes.

523
00:41:39,413 --> 00:41:41,248
I see.

524
00:41:46,921 --> 00:41:51,133
That it didn't matter to me
whatever happened to someone else's life.

525
00:41:51,634 --> 00:41:52,927
Come on, Master!

526
00:41:53,010 --> 00:41:55,262
You're really gonna run for it,
aren't you?

527
00:42:02,728 --> 00:42:03,812
Such annoying,

528
00:42:05,189 --> 00:42:06,899
bothersome people.

529
00:42:08,692 --> 00:42:09,777
Mr. Oddball.

530
00:42:09,860 --> 00:42:12,655
We get it, all right?
You're not exactly happy to see us.

531
00:42:12,738 --> 00:42:13,781
This guy won't give up!

532
00:42:13,864 --> 00:42:15,407
But we still like you, Master.

533
00:42:16,492 --> 00:42:19,203
Most people don't bother
if they don't want to help.

534
00:42:19,286 --> 00:42:21,455
But even if you don't want to,

535
00:42:21,539 --> 00:42:23,165
you help in the end.

536
00:42:23,958 --> 00:42:24,875
Know why?

537
00:42:26,335 --> 00:42:27,878
Because you're on my side.

538
00:42:27,962 --> 00:42:29,755
Master!

539
00:42:30,297 --> 00:42:31,966
No concept of personal space

540
00:42:32,758 --> 00:42:34,969
in the way they just keep barging in.

541
00:42:41,600 --> 00:42:42,685
I wanted to find her.

542
00:42:46,063 --> 00:42:48,774
And I wanted to know
what it was that I'd lost.

543
00:42:53,195 --> 00:42:54,822
I thought that if I found my mom…

544
00:42:59,785 --> 00:43:01,662
I could turn my life around…

545
00:43:04,331 --> 00:43:06,125
even just a little bit.

546
00:43:15,092 --> 00:43:16,176
That's why.

547
00:43:19,346 --> 00:43:20,598
That's why I…

548
00:44:02,306 --> 00:44:04,183
Such ridiculously…

549
00:44:06,018 --> 00:44:07,227
warm

550
00:44:08,729 --> 00:44:10,147
and friendly people.

551
00:44:11,440 --> 00:44:12,274
Why? What?

552
00:44:12,775 --> 00:44:14,151
Did I tick you off?

553
00:44:21,784 --> 00:44:25,245
What, are you calling the Church?
To tell them to kidnap us too?

554
00:44:27,081 --> 00:44:28,332
I need people.

555
00:44:30,000 --> 00:44:30,876
How many?

556
00:44:30,959 --> 00:44:32,711
The more, the better.

557
00:44:33,212 --> 00:44:34,088
A hundred?

558
00:44:35,214 --> 00:44:36,674
No, make that 200.

559
00:44:39,802 --> 00:44:40,886
You got it.

560
00:44:44,682 --> 00:44:46,058
I'm sorry, Mr. Yang.

561
00:44:46,141 --> 00:44:47,434
Please, just this once.

562
00:44:47,518 --> 00:44:50,646
After you up and left as though you were
never going to see us again?

563
00:44:50,729 --> 00:44:53,857
Guess some people's antisocial tendencies
rubbed off on you.

564
00:44:53,941 --> 00:44:54,817
Anti…

565
00:44:54,900 --> 00:44:56,068
What?

566
00:45:03,784 --> 00:45:04,952
Please.

567
00:45:09,707 --> 00:45:10,874
PUBLIC HOUSING DEPARTMENT

568
00:45:12,751 --> 00:45:16,046
Victory! Get the job done!
Class 560, Yang Seok-u!

569
00:45:16,130 --> 00:45:16,964
Victory!

570
00:45:17,673 --> 00:45:19,425
- What is it?
- Some energy drinks, sir.

571
00:45:19,508 --> 00:45:20,342
Thanks, but--

572
00:45:20,426 --> 00:45:22,469
Allow me to just use your computer.

573
00:45:22,553 --> 00:45:24,638
"Church of…" Stop right there.

574
00:45:24,722 --> 00:45:26,849
You're poking the hornet's nest!
Take this back.

575
00:45:26,932 --> 00:45:29,184
How about some liquor?
Your favorite hard liquor.

576
00:45:29,268 --> 00:45:31,687
- Bomb shots?
- Yes, bomb shots, sir.

577
00:45:31,770 --> 00:45:34,148
- Well, that is…
- Okay, great.

578
00:45:34,732 --> 00:45:36,024
SWEET HOME WELFARE CENTER

579
00:45:36,108 --> 00:45:37,484
CHURCH OF ETERNAL SALVATION

580
00:45:37,568 --> 00:45:39,862
Floor plans
of the Church of Eternal Salvation.

581
00:45:41,655 --> 00:45:42,656
Thank you, Mr. Yang.

582
00:45:44,241 --> 00:45:45,701
So you even smile, huh?

583
00:45:45,784 --> 00:45:48,203
You finally seem human.

584
00:45:48,287 --> 00:45:49,955
I always figured

585
00:45:50,038 --> 00:45:53,500
you had a compartment on your back
to insert batteries or something.

586
00:45:58,964 --> 00:46:01,800
Actually, I'm… the rechargeable kind.

587
00:46:08,724 --> 00:46:09,975
220 volts.

588
00:46:22,613 --> 00:46:24,198
This area is too open.

589
00:46:25,324 --> 00:46:28,994
As for this side, it'll be hard
to secure a route to the drain.

590
00:46:35,959 --> 00:46:38,253
Let's just report it to the cops.

591
00:46:38,337 --> 00:46:41,006
This is beyond our scope.

592
00:46:41,089 --> 00:46:42,174
And what would we say?

593
00:46:43,383 --> 00:46:44,343
Goddammit.

594
00:46:44,927 --> 00:46:47,554
What else? We tell the truth,
whether they believe or not.

595
00:46:47,638 --> 00:46:50,390
Then we'll have done our part,
and we can walk away.

596
00:46:51,558 --> 00:46:52,935
They won't believe us anyway.

597
00:46:53,435 --> 00:46:56,563
The first thing those people do
is silence the police.

598
00:46:56,647 --> 00:46:58,607
All the more reason for us to stay put.

599
00:46:58,690 --> 00:47:01,318
If the police can't do anything about it,
what can we do?

600
00:47:01,401 --> 00:47:03,529
Who are you to get involved?

601
00:47:05,405 --> 00:47:06,698
Chae-ni is my friend!

602
00:47:07,825 --> 00:47:09,409
And I will save her.

603
00:47:11,203 --> 00:47:13,705
So you went from a toddler
to a 30-year-old muscle man,

604
00:47:13,789 --> 00:47:15,624
but what can you actually do?

605
00:47:15,707 --> 00:47:19,586
That superpower just about
puts you on par with other people now.

606
00:47:19,670 --> 00:47:21,839
So what could you possibly do?

607
00:47:21,922 --> 00:47:25,175
You seem to be under the delusion
that you've become something amazing,

608
00:47:25,759 --> 00:47:28,053
but compared to the Wunderkinder,
you're a rookie.

609
00:47:28,136 --> 00:47:29,847
If you value your life,

610
00:47:29,930 --> 00:47:32,683
just stay put and don't get involved.

611
00:47:32,766 --> 00:47:35,143
Even if you get involved,
there's nothing you--

612
00:47:45,237 --> 00:47:47,322
I guess there's a lot you could do.

613
00:47:50,701 --> 00:47:52,661
Now it's time to train in real life.

614
00:47:52,744 --> 00:47:54,371
How can we trust you?

615
00:47:55,163 --> 00:47:57,291
We never know
when you'll become Mr. Curveball.

616
00:47:57,374 --> 00:48:00,002
What if we all go in to save her,
and you change your mind?

617
00:48:00,085 --> 00:48:00,919
Yes, fine.

618
00:48:01,003 --> 00:48:04,506
I know the situation right now
is urgent and desperate,

619
00:48:05,007 --> 00:48:06,925
but should we risk our lives for her?

620
00:48:07,009 --> 00:48:10,846
Hey, Kang Ro-bin, say something.
This just isn't right.

621
00:48:10,929 --> 00:48:12,389
Back the fudge off.

622
00:48:13,557 --> 00:48:15,017
What's with the stink eye?

623
00:48:15,100 --> 00:48:17,978
When you, of all people,
look at me like that,

624
00:48:18,061 --> 00:48:20,856
it makes me feel so darn pathetic.

625
00:48:20,939 --> 00:48:23,734
You do seem pretty darn pathetic.

626
00:48:25,110 --> 00:48:27,446
Let's go, Master. Just us.

627
00:48:27,529 --> 00:48:28,363
Hey.

628
00:48:28,447 --> 00:48:31,074
Wait. Who said I wasn't going?

629
00:48:31,158 --> 00:48:32,409
Okay, fine.

630
00:48:33,535 --> 00:48:34,578
Got it. I'll go.

631
00:48:34,661 --> 00:48:35,954
I'm going.

632
00:48:36,455 --> 00:48:38,081
But on one condition.

633
00:48:41,084 --> 00:48:43,295
We file the police report in my name.

634
00:48:47,215 --> 00:48:48,050
Deal!

635
00:49:12,115 --> 00:49:12,991
HAESEONG CITY HALL

636
00:49:25,921 --> 00:49:27,339
My code name will be

637
00:49:27,839 --> 00:49:30,092
"Condolence Wreath."

638
00:49:31,176 --> 00:49:34,972
Do you think we can get there
before they wrench out Chae-ni's heart?

639
00:49:35,722 --> 00:49:36,640
Enough chatter.

640
00:49:37,140 --> 00:49:40,477
Let's get moving. If we're too late,
this will all have been for nothing.

641
00:49:46,650 --> 00:49:48,026
EUN CHAE-NI

642
00:50:40,746 --> 00:50:41,705
This is infuriating!

643
00:50:43,874 --> 00:50:45,751
What exactly is going on out there?

644
00:50:46,293 --> 00:50:49,296
Why are they keeping us in here
and not letting us go outside?

645
00:50:50,130 --> 00:50:51,339
Know anything, Ju-ran?

646
00:50:54,301 --> 00:50:56,219
I think Father found that child.

647
00:50:56,303 --> 00:50:57,596
That child?

648
00:50:59,056 --> 00:51:01,308
You mean the Child of Eternity?
He found him?

649
00:51:04,061 --> 00:51:06,021
Then why didn't he tell us?

650
00:51:06,104 --> 00:51:08,982
If he found him,
he should have called us first.

651
00:51:09,691 --> 00:51:11,193
Isn't this a bit odd?

652
00:51:11,276 --> 00:51:12,694
Don't you two agree?

653
00:51:12,778 --> 00:51:14,154
I'm sure he has a reason.

654
00:51:15,113 --> 00:51:15,947
Just wait.

655
00:51:17,949 --> 00:51:19,743
You know what Father hates most.

656
00:51:20,702 --> 00:51:22,162
Asking unnecessary questions.

657
00:51:28,585 --> 00:51:30,837
We could listen in another way.

658
00:51:36,051 --> 00:51:37,010
You don't mean…

659
00:51:37,594 --> 00:51:38,512
Are you insane?

660
00:51:45,811 --> 00:51:47,938
- Father.
- I'm busy now. Later.

661
00:51:48,021 --> 00:51:50,315
We heard you found the Child of Eternity.

662
00:51:56,530 --> 00:51:58,115
Please tell us.

663
00:51:59,199 --> 00:52:01,243
Why are you hiding that child from us?

664
00:52:01,326 --> 00:52:03,203
What exactly are you suspecting?

665
00:52:10,127 --> 00:52:11,586
Tell us.

666
00:52:12,629 --> 00:52:14,714
What are you hiding from us?

667
00:52:21,930 --> 00:52:23,265
Answer me.

668
00:52:25,475 --> 00:52:27,227
Please answer me, Father.

669
00:52:42,367 --> 00:52:43,618
"Now faith is

670
00:52:45,537 --> 00:52:47,789
confidence in what we hope for

671
00:52:48,290 --> 00:52:51,251
and assurance about what we do not see."

672
00:52:54,671 --> 00:52:56,131
If you do not have faith in me,

673
00:52:56,214 --> 00:53:00,218
you'll never be able to see
what you hope for, Ju-ran.

674
00:53:10,395 --> 00:53:13,732
You possess the ability
that I love most of all.

675
00:53:14,232 --> 00:53:17,152
It's also the ability I need the most.

676
00:53:17,736 --> 00:53:18,987
But that doesn't mean

677
00:53:19,946 --> 00:53:22,032
you can use it on me.

678
00:53:31,208 --> 00:53:32,959
Elder Yoon has been in touch.

679
00:53:33,043 --> 00:53:35,545
He says there is a crowd gathered
outside the building.

680
00:53:35,629 --> 00:53:37,964
Didn't you hear there's been a problem?

681
00:53:39,007 --> 00:53:39,841
You should go.

682
00:53:58,652 --> 00:54:01,488
You are my daughter of faith, Ju-ran.

683
00:54:03,281 --> 00:54:05,825
As you are my first child,

684
00:54:06,993 --> 00:54:09,246
I will save you before anyone else.

685
00:54:11,706 --> 00:54:12,832
So,

686
00:54:12,916 --> 00:54:15,252
do not test me.

687
00:54:16,836 --> 00:54:20,840
Doubt and distrust
will only rot your bones.

688
00:54:25,512 --> 00:54:26,346
Yes,

689
00:54:27,472 --> 00:54:28,306
Father.

690
00:54:44,114 --> 00:54:46,992
Give us back our families!

691
00:54:47,075 --> 00:54:49,744
Give them back!

692
00:54:49,828 --> 00:54:51,955
Cultists, begone!

693
00:54:52,038 --> 00:54:54,416
Begone!

694
00:54:54,499 --> 00:54:56,626
Give us back our families!

695
00:54:56,710 --> 00:54:58,670
Give them back!

696
00:54:58,753 --> 00:55:00,880
Cultists, begone!

697
00:55:00,964 --> 00:55:02,340
Begone!

698
00:55:02,424 --> 00:55:03,675
Please save them all.

699
00:55:03,758 --> 00:55:06,594
A criminal organization
that brainwashes people!

700
00:55:06,678 --> 00:55:07,846
Leave!

701
00:55:07,929 --> 00:55:09,681
Leave!

702
00:55:09,764 --> 00:55:12,183
- Please save them all.
- Give us back our families!

703
00:55:12,267 --> 00:55:14,686
Give them back!

704
00:55:14,769 --> 00:55:16,730
Cultists, begone!

705
00:55:16,813 --> 00:55:19,065
Begone!

706
00:55:19,149 --> 00:55:20,859
Give us back our families!

707
00:55:20,942 --> 00:55:22,485
Did you contact the police?

708
00:55:23,403 --> 00:55:24,237
Yes.

709
00:55:24,321 --> 00:55:25,905
They said they're on their way.

710
00:55:25,989 --> 00:55:28,199
Begone!

711
00:55:28,283 --> 00:55:30,785
Give us back our families!

712
00:55:30,869 --> 00:55:32,787
Give them back!

713
00:55:32,871 --> 00:55:36,249
- Cultists, begone!
- Begone!

714
00:55:36,333 --> 00:55:40,920
- Give us back our families!
- Give them back!

715
00:55:41,421 --> 00:55:44,215
The Church is a criminal organization
that brainwashes people!

716
00:55:44,299 --> 00:55:47,969
Leave!

717
00:55:48,053 --> 00:55:49,387
All right, everyone!

718
00:55:49,471 --> 00:55:53,183
Let's let them hear our screams, our fury!

719
00:56:24,130 --> 00:56:25,465
Thanks.

720
00:56:29,135 --> 00:56:30,428
I'm Number 4204.

721
00:56:35,141 --> 00:56:36,684
Thanks to the fire that day,

722
00:56:37,268 --> 00:56:39,479
I got out just before
they experimented on me.

723
00:56:40,772 --> 00:56:43,066
There were 20 other kids like me.

724
00:56:43,650 --> 00:56:44,609
Thanks to you,

725
00:56:45,402 --> 00:56:47,112
we're all okay and living our lives.

726
00:56:50,240 --> 00:56:51,449
If you need this…

727
00:56:56,663 --> 00:56:57,580
That's okay.

728
00:57:31,781 --> 00:57:32,949
They're all in.

729
00:57:40,081 --> 00:57:41,249
HAESEONG POLICE STATION

730
00:58:14,115 --> 00:58:15,408
Why did you bring this?

731
00:59:08,461 --> 00:59:09,337
What?

732
00:59:35,780 --> 00:59:37,198
Brother Hyeong-rok.

733
00:59:38,157 --> 00:59:39,534
Brother Su-hyeok!

734
00:59:41,786 --> 00:59:44,455
Come on out already.
I really hate this kind of thing.

735
00:59:50,044 --> 00:59:51,588
I love you. C'mere.

736
00:59:57,218 --> 00:59:59,429
Actually, I don't. So piss off!

737
01:00:01,014 --> 01:00:02,390
Sorry.

738
01:00:10,773 --> 01:00:14,569
I won't bother mentioning that this is
all thanks to my flypaper hands.

739
01:00:15,320 --> 01:00:17,447
Master, which way do we go now?

740
01:00:19,032 --> 01:00:20,199
Hold on a second.

741
01:00:22,952 --> 01:00:24,454
There's a door here.

742
01:00:25,705 --> 01:00:26,581
Come here.

743
01:00:27,290 --> 01:00:28,750
We can just open it.

744
01:00:34,797 --> 01:00:36,257
What is it?

745
01:00:36,758 --> 01:00:37,759
I can't see a thing.

746
01:00:49,437 --> 01:00:50,521
Hello, sirs.

747
01:00:52,440 --> 01:00:55,693
Why haven't you disbanded them yet?
Even the police are here.

748
01:00:56,194 --> 01:00:58,237
We did send some officers--

749
01:00:58,905 --> 01:01:00,365
OUTDOOR ASSEMBLY PERMIT FORM

750
01:01:01,407 --> 01:01:03,993
"They're exercising
their right and freedom to assemble."

751
01:01:04,494 --> 01:01:05,662
Explain it like that.

752
01:01:10,208 --> 01:01:13,252
After all the money
they gobbled up from us?

753
01:01:18,383 --> 01:01:19,217
What is it?

754
01:01:21,094 --> 01:01:23,596
We have intruders.

755
01:01:26,766 --> 01:01:29,602
- Cultists, begone!
- Begone!

756
01:01:30,186 --> 01:01:32,313
Pal-ho!

757
01:01:57,296 --> 01:01:59,257
What's that old geezer

758
01:01:59,757 --> 01:02:01,801
doing over there?

759
01:02:02,510 --> 01:02:04,137
We'll be transplanting

760
01:02:04,762 --> 01:02:06,264
your heart into him.

761
01:02:11,310 --> 01:02:13,938
But you said I'd be saving the world.

762
01:02:15,898 --> 01:02:17,233
You said…

763
01:02:19,569 --> 01:02:21,612
that in exchange for my life,

764
01:02:22,363 --> 01:02:24,699
you could save countless others.

765
01:02:27,076 --> 01:02:28,327
But you're just

766
01:02:29,912 --> 01:02:31,998
giving it to that old man?

767
01:02:34,167 --> 01:02:36,294
No need to feel wronged, child.

768
01:02:36,794 --> 01:02:39,630
The only truths that exist in this world

769
01:02:40,339 --> 01:02:42,759
are unfair, unreasonable,

770
01:02:43,843 --> 01:02:45,928
and unpleasant ones.

771
01:02:46,971 --> 01:02:48,556
No.

772
01:02:49,474 --> 01:02:50,850
Still, this isn't

773
01:02:51,809 --> 01:02:53,770
what you told me earlier.

774
01:02:54,896 --> 01:02:57,315
Why should I die

775
01:02:57,899 --> 01:02:59,692
just to save that old man?

776
01:03:00,193 --> 01:03:01,027
Why?

777
01:03:01,527 --> 01:03:02,904
Because you

778
01:03:03,488 --> 01:03:04,989
are nothing.

779
01:03:12,705 --> 01:03:13,998
Die.

780
01:03:14,874 --> 01:03:16,709
Die…

781
01:03:18,377 --> 01:03:19,378
Gladly.

782
01:03:23,424 --> 01:03:24,675
Gladly…

783
01:03:27,553 --> 01:03:29,597
But I don't want to die.

784
01:03:35,311 --> 01:03:36,562
Why…

785
01:03:37,522 --> 01:03:40,107
Why am I nothing?

786
01:03:41,943 --> 01:03:43,319
I am

787
01:03:44,862 --> 01:03:46,072
my grandma's…

788
01:03:48,491 --> 01:03:51,118
entire world.

789
01:03:53,663 --> 01:03:54,997
And I'm Ro-bin's…

790
01:03:57,708 --> 01:04:01,379
one and only friend.

791
01:04:04,173 --> 01:04:06,008
And I'm Mr. Son's…

792
01:04:08,886 --> 01:04:11,180
adrenaline kick.

793
01:04:13,224 --> 01:04:14,642
And

794
01:04:16,352 --> 01:04:17,478
Master.

795
01:04:22,525 --> 01:04:24,610
I'm Master's…

796
01:04:40,376 --> 01:04:42,003
I'm Master's…

797
01:05:11,532 --> 01:05:13,326
I'm not wild about the idea, but you're

798
01:05:14,952 --> 01:05:15,828
on my side.

799
01:05:43,481 --> 01:05:44,482
Where is she?

800
01:05:44,565 --> 01:05:45,441
Is that her?

801
01:05:45,524 --> 01:05:47,068
Hey, is that white thing Chae-ni?

802
01:05:47,151 --> 01:05:48,361
Chae-ni!

803
01:05:48,861 --> 01:05:51,364
- Chae-ni!
- Eun Chae-ni!

804
01:05:51,948 --> 01:05:53,783
- Chae-ni.
- Oh no, what do we do?

805
01:05:53,866 --> 01:05:56,035
Chae-ni! Are you conscious or not?

806
01:05:56,118 --> 01:05:58,746
It's me, Mr. Son. Are you okay?

807
01:05:59,705 --> 01:06:00,623
- Chae-ni!
- Oh no!

808
01:06:01,207 --> 01:06:04,001
- Chae-ni!
- Get this damn thing out of my face.

809
01:06:05,962 --> 01:06:07,129
Have we untied her?

810
01:06:09,423 --> 01:06:10,841
Stop!

811
01:06:15,054 --> 01:06:16,222
What was that?

812
01:06:20,351 --> 01:06:21,227
Mr. Son, hurry!

813
01:06:21,310 --> 01:06:22,645
- What do we do?
- Hurry up!

814
01:06:22,728 --> 01:06:23,688
What's going on?

815
01:06:25,064 --> 01:06:27,650
What do we do? Give that to me. All right!

816
01:06:29,610 --> 01:06:31,320
Hello. Call me Moon Mi-hui.

817
01:06:40,997 --> 01:06:42,790
- Here!
- Ro-bin!

818
01:06:55,636 --> 01:06:57,138
You bastard!

819
01:07:14,030 --> 01:07:15,781
- Chae-ni, are you okay?
- You okay?

820
01:07:16,657 --> 01:07:19,285
Damn you, Lady Trainwreck!

821
01:07:19,368 --> 01:07:20,536
My eyes!

822
01:07:21,078 --> 01:07:22,747
I can't see!

823
01:07:33,007 --> 01:07:34,467
Hey, catch her!

824
01:08:26,435 --> 01:08:28,479
I guess you felt a little bad.

825
01:08:29,063 --> 01:08:30,773
I'm not saving you for your sake

826
01:08:31,565 --> 01:08:33,567
but for theirs.

827
01:08:36,987 --> 01:08:38,697
Because when you hold a grudge,

828
01:08:40,324 --> 01:08:41,534
you're persistent.

829
01:08:43,494 --> 01:08:45,955
Why don't you get out of my face, then?

830
01:08:46,038 --> 01:08:47,456
Before I really hold a grudge.

831
01:08:54,213 --> 01:08:55,047
No.

832
01:09:08,018 --> 01:09:10,437
Did she really poke my eyes out
or something?

833
01:09:10,938 --> 01:09:12,481
What am I seeing?

834
01:09:18,946 --> 01:09:20,281
You go, Ms. Eun Chae-ni.

835
01:09:21,699 --> 01:09:22,658
To a safe place.

836
01:09:42,720 --> 01:09:44,180
- Of course.
- Again.

837
01:09:45,514 --> 01:09:46,432
Of course.

838
01:09:55,107 --> 01:09:56,817
What… What's this?

839
01:10:05,367 --> 01:10:07,745
How could Lady Trainwreck
disappear all by herself?

840
01:10:07,828 --> 01:10:10,497
This is why they say
people bite the hands who feed

841
01:10:10,581 --> 01:10:12,458
or desert the friends who save you.

842
01:10:16,879 --> 01:10:20,341
Mr. Son. If you're scared,
just hurl insults at me from behind.

843
01:10:21,383 --> 01:10:22,676
You bastard, son of a bitch.

844
01:10:22,760 --> 01:10:26,013
You potato-looking sap
with your corduroy pants. That do it?

845
01:11:14,144 --> 01:11:17,564
But you're nothing.

846
01:11:18,524 --> 01:11:19,441
No.

847
01:11:20,317 --> 01:11:22,194
It's not that I'm nothing.

848
01:11:22,987 --> 01:11:25,489
I just haven't done anything yet.

849
01:14:55,824 --> 01:15:00,829
Subtitle translation by: Jimin Choi
